20.4 Securely copying files
scp can be used to securely copy files over the network, using the sshd process

scp file1 file2 student@remoteserver:/home/student

scp -r root@remoteserver:/tmp/files - -r is for recursive. this will copy the contents of /tmp/files to the current dir

sftp offers an ftp client interface to securely transfer files using sshd
	use put /my/file to upload a file
	use get /your/gile to download to the current directory
	use exit at the end of your ftp session

